Adrenal carcinoma presenting as a lesion resembling cutaneous angiosarcoma.
 A case is reported of adrenal carcinoma presenting as an angiosarcoma-like metastasis in the scalp.
 Adrenal carcinoma is a rare tumor, and it metastasizes to skin rarely.
 The authors discuss the features of this tumor that led to a diagnosis of angiosarcoma and the means by which such a metastasis may be distinguished from vascular tumors.
